It is a nice day.

536
00:20:26,020 --> 00:20:28,040
Missed our chance again!

537
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:29,190
Looks like we're
a little too late.

538
00:20:29,190 --> 00:20:32,210
(groaning)

539
00:20:32,210 --> 00:20:34,090
-Women.
-Scary.

540
00:20:34,090 --> 00:20:35,250
Hey, you two!

541
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,220
Hold it right there!

542
00:20:37,220 --> 00:20:39,020
-Run!
-Again?

543
00:20:39,020 --> 00:20:40,070
You come back here.

544
00:20:40,070 --> 00:20:41,070
Right now!

545
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:42,280
-Wait, no, we're--
-Innocent!

546
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:51,130
Hello!

547
00:20:51,130 --> 00:20:52,280
♪

548
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:55,170
Hey, we're back!

549
00:20:55,170 --> 00:20:58,180
Welcome home, ladies,
I hope it was a good day.

550
00:20:58,180 --> 00:21:01,270
Oh, yes, a lot of things
turned out just fine.

551
00:21:01,270 --> 00:21:03,150
One of the greatest
pleasures we have

552
00:21:03,150 --> 00:21:05,060
is remembering good days.

553
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:07,240
Kenshin, you're right.

554
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:12,040
(blowing air)

555
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:14,170
Yours,
souvenir.

556
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:16,080
A paper balloon?

557
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:19,020
You bought me one just
like this a long time ago.

558
00:21:19,020 --> 00:21:22,170
I just felt like
returning the favor to you.

559
00:21:22,170 --> 00:21:24,290
You know, you haven't
changed a bit, Misao.

560
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:27,020
Actually, Aoshi, I did.

561
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:29,080
When you weren't paying
attention, I grew up.

562
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:33,080
♪

563
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:34,260
I'm a woman.

564
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:36,230
We could talk about
that if you like.

565
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:40,060
♪

566
00:21:40,060 --> 00:21:43,170
Yes, I'd like that a lot.

567
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:45,010
Kenshin, there's
something really different

568
00:21:45,010 --> 00:21:47,000
about Aoshi from this morning.

569
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,100
Well, it could be
that his vision's

570
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:50,110
become a little
more contemporary.

571
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:51,150
Hmm?

572
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:53,070
(panting)

573
00:21:53,070 --> 00:21:55,180
-Sano!
-Yoshi!

574
00:21:55,180 --> 00:21:56,270
Where have
you two been?

575
00:21:56,270 --> 00:21:57,270
Why were
you running?

576
00:21:57,270 --> 00:21:58,270
Are you all right?

577
00:21:58,270 --> 00:21:59,270
No.

578
00:21:59,270 --> 00:22:00,270
Not really.

579
00:22:00,270 --> 00:22:02,090
Something's
not right here.

580
00:22:02,090 --> 00:22:04,020
Are you hungry,
Sanosuke?

581
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:06,000
Here's some hard
crackers to nibble on.

582
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,200
No, no thank you.

583
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,280
Oh, you poor baby.

584
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:10,120
You must have
a bad tummy ache.

585
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,200
I'm fine.

586
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,280
Tomorrow,
we go back to Kyoto!

587
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:15,170
-Oh!
-What's the matter?

588
00:22:15,170 --> 00:22:16,220
In all the excitement,

589
00:22:16,220 --> 00:22:18,210
we forgot to get
Okina's souvenir today.

590
00:22:18,210 --> 00:22:19,250
Oh, no.

591
00:22:19,250 --> 00:22:21,110
Well, we'll just
go back tomorrow

592
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:22,110
and get one for him.

593
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:23,200
-No!
-No way!

594
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,290
Why on Earth not?

595
00:22:24,290 --> 00:22:27,250
Because, Kaoru, nothing good
comes of these trips to town.

596
00:22:27,250 --> 00:22:28,250
What do you mean?

597
00:22:28,250 --> 00:22:30,040
What did you do?

598
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:31,060
Nothing!

599
00:22:31,060 --> 00:22:32,090
Why don't I believe you?

600
00:22:32,090 --> 00:22:33,210
Tell me what you did.

601
00:22:33,210 --> 00:22:35,010
I did nothing, I swear.

602
00:22:35,010 --> 00:22:36,100
I'm innocent.

603
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:37,120
We weren't following you.

604
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:38,160
Come on, tell 'em Yoshi.

605
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:39,603
Tell 'em!

606
00:22:40,583 --> 00:25:02,941
♪

607
00:25:04,841 --> 00:25:06,901
♪

